data.title: Beaconsfield Historical Society
data.text:
Leaflet for Western Front Association.

The Western Front Association formed to recognise those who fell in the First World War from both sides. Activities and membership subscriptions via Derek Bracey for the Ox and Bucks Branch.

G-C/B/005

Leaflet titled "The Charters of the Fair and of the Market"

Souvenir leaflet of transcript and translation of Latin text from Charter Rolls granting the right to the nuns and abbess of Burnham Abbey to hold an annual Charter Fair in 1269 and the right to a Market to Richard Earl of Cornwall, Lord of the Manor, in 1255 in Beaconsfield

B-BA/B/002

Leather-bound ledger containing particulars of properties offered for sale/lease by A. C. Frost & Co

Leather-bound ledger containing particulars of properties offered for sale / lease in Beaconsfield and district. Notable properties include: ‘The Retreat’ and ‘Farmside’ Reynolds Road, Beaconsfield (p502/3). Huntley Cottage, Baring Road. ‘Maryton’ Burkes Road, offered for sale in 1929 for £2700. (p510). ‘Byethorn’, Sandelswood End at a price of £2300 in 1951.(p511). ‘Roselands’, Beechwood ...

O-F/B/005

Ledborough Lane Wikipedia

Photocopy of a print out of ‘Ledborough’. Detailing that Ledborough was a hamlet in the parish of Beaconsfield which became incorporated into the town of Beaconsfield in the early 20th century

G-BG/A/032

Leigh House

Collection of articles, letters, research notes etc extracted from various sources and passed to the Beaconsfield and District Historical Society relating to Leigh House.

B-LH

Letter from L. Brits to Mr H. Crane

Letter of 29/6/93 from L. Brits to Mr Crane; in reply from a request from him on information and the origin of Beaconsfield in Kimberley. Also mentions are near by mining villages: Bultfontein, Dutoitspan (Beaconsfield), Pniel and Klipdrift. Kimberley was also originally New Rush and Klipdrift became Barkly West in 1873. Enclosed are 2 maps ...

P-HC/L/009

Letter and attachment from Arnold Kramish to Miss Williams at the Beaconsfield Historical Society.

Typed letter from Arnold Kramish requesting information on Wilton Park which he referred to as the British MI9 and IS9 headquarters. Attached is a brochure entitled ‘The Griffin’ which details the story of Paul Rosbaud, Britain’s Master Spy in Nazi Germany.

G-Mil/L/001

Letter and 2 maps regarding land adjacent to the A40 involving the access to the proposed M40 compulsory purchase Order from the Hall Barn Estate

Copy of Conveyance and annotated map regarding land adjacent to the A40 involving the access to the proposed M40. Letter from Ministry of Transport to Wilton Park Estates noting the ownership change 1934 from the Wilton Park to Council.

B-M40/L/045

Letter dated 5 July 1993 from JW Bourke, the General Manager of The Council of the City of South Sydney, containing details of the history of Beaconsfield Sydney

A letter addressed to Mr Crane of the Beaconsfield Historical Society containing details of Beaconsfield in Sydney and it’s history. Includes maps of the boundary of Beaconsfield Sydney and documents on the history of Beaconsfield.

P-HC/L/011
